  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to team-lead's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "steve-krug",
    "senderColor": "cyan",
    "target": "@team-lead",
    "targetColor": "red",
    "summary": "CONSENT on Task #3 DoD update",
    "content": "**CONSENT** from Steve Krug (UX Specialist) on Task #3.\n\nThe two Product DoD additions are exactly the usability checks I care about:\n\n1. **\"User can complete a full journey from the landing page through the feature being delivered\"** -- This is the Trunk Test applied to the whole flow, not just a single page. It catches exactly the kind of dead-end problem we just fixed on the index page. If someone builds a feature but you can't reach it from the front door, it's not done.\n\n2. **\"All navigation paths lead somewhere useful (no dead-end pages)\"** -- This codifies what should have caught the original index page problem before it shipped. Every link, every button, every form submission should leave the user somewhere they can take their next action.\n\nBoth are simple, concrete, and testable. They don't add process overhead -- they just make explicit what \"done\" should have always meant from a usability standpoint."
  }
}
